  "text": "Google Pixel Tablet $279 $399 Save $120 Brand Google Storage 128GB or 256GB CPU Google Tensor G2 Memory 8GB LPDDR5 RAM Operating System Android 14 Looking for a smart home hub that can double as a gaming tablet? Google's Pixel Tablet fits the bill. ItÂ flaunts a 10.9-inch IPS LCD screen, backed by the power of the Google Tensor G2 chipset and 8GB RAM for a snappy experience. Its camera setup includes an 8 MP rear and front camera, perfect for capturing those spontaneous moments or crystal-clear video calls. The Pixel Tablet is one of the best tablets you can buy right now if you're looking for Google's Android experience. Not only do you get a tablet that's sleek with good performance, but you're also going to get a good display, along with a discount that drops it well below its original $399 price tag. Related Google Pixel Tablet review: That first-gen feeling It's a fine midranger, but the Pixel Tablet's best ideas are half-baked For a limited time, you can score a hefty $120 discount that knocks the Pixel Tablet down to $279. This is one of the best prices we've seen on this tablet, making it a great time to pick one up. We know that Prime Day is just around the corner, but we don't think that the price of this tablet will get any better. So grab it now if you've been looking for a new Android tablet and save big. What's great about the Pixel Tablet? The Pixel Tablet was Google's first modern attempt at an Android tablet. And while it didn't get everything right, it was still a pretty good piece of hardware. You get a vibrant 11-inch screen and powerful processor with Google's Tensor G2 chip that's paired with 8GB of RAM and 128GB of internal storage. The software is also smooth, and you can run pretty much anything you need to on this tablet, whether you're looking at productivity apps or even games. Of course, you also have cameras on this tablet as well, which can be used to capture the moment or have a video call with family, friends or even colleagues. Overall, this isn't a bad tablet to go with if you've been looking for something affordable and by Google. It isn't the latest tablet on the market, but there's still plenty left in the tank, especially with Google's reliable track record when it comes to software updates. Get it now for just $279 while this deal's still live.",
