                                                                                                                      \n            \n                                                \n                        \n            \n            \n                                        \n                                        \u003csource media=\"(min-width: 0px)\" data-srcset=\"https://static1.anpoimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/google-pixel-tablet-homescreen-on-stand.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=432\u0026amp;h=260\u0026amp;dpr=2\" srcset=\"https://static1.anpoimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/google-pixel-tablet-homescreen-on-stand.jpg?q=49\u0026amp;fit=crop\u0026amp;w=432\u0026amp;h=260\u0026amp;dpr=2\"/\u003e\n                    \n                    \u003cimg width=\"2000\" height=\"1333\" loading=\"lazy\" decoding=\"async\" alt=\"A powered-on tablet on a stand, sitting on a table in front of a window\" data-img-url=\"https://static1.anpoimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/google-pixel-tablet-homescreen-on-stand.jpg\" src=\"https://static1.anpoimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2023/06/google-pixel-tablet-homescreen-on-stand.jpg\"/\u003e\n        \n    \u003c/picture\u003e\n                \n    \u003c/figure\u003e\n\n\n        \u003c/div\u003e\n\n\t\t\u003c/a\u003e\n\t\n\n        \n                    \u003cp\u003e\u003cspan data-field=\"label\"\u003eRelated\u003c/span\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003cdiv\u003e\n\n                \n                 \n                \t\n\t\n\u003ch5\u003e\n\t\n\n\t\t\t\t\t        \t\t\t\t\n\t\t\u003ca href=\"https://www.androidpolice.com/google-pixel-tablet-review/\" title=\"Google Pixel Tablet review: That first-gen feeling\" target=\"_blank\"\u003e\n\t\t\tGoogle Pixel Tablet review: That first-gen feeling\n\t\t\u003c/a\u003e\n\t\u003c/h5\u003e\n\n                                                    \n                \t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\u003cp\u003eIt\u0026#39;s a fine midranger, but the Pixel Tablet\u0026#39;s best ideas are half-baked\u003c/p\u003e\n\t\t\t\n\n                    \n\n\n                \n                \n                \n                \n\n                \n                \n                \n                \t\n\n\n                \n\n                \n                \n                \n            \u003c/div\u003e\n                \n        \n        \n        \n            \u003c/div\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eFor a limited time, you can score a hefty $120 discount that knocks the Pixel Tablet down to $279. This is one of the best prices we\u0026#39;ve seen on this tablet, making it a great time to pick one up. We know that \u003ca href=\"https://www.androidpolice.com/amazon-prime-day-2025-summer-event-july-8-to-july-11/\" target=\"_blank\"\u003ePrime Day is just around the corner\u003c/a\u003e, but we don\u0026#39;t think that the price of this tablet will get any better. So grab it now if you\u0026#39;ve been looking for a new Android tablet and save big. \u003c/p\u003e    \u003cp\u003e\u003ca href=\"https://www.androidpolice.com/amazon-prime-day-2025/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\"\u003e\n\u003cimg alt=\"Amazon Prime Day 2025 promotional banner from Android Police\" src=\"https://static0.anpoimages.com/wordpress/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/img_0103.png\"/\u003e\n \u003c/a\u003e\u003c/p\u003e\u003ch2 id=\"what-39-s-great-about-the-pixel-tablet\"\u003e\n                        What\u0026#39;s great about the Pixel Tablet?\n               \u003c/h2\u003e    \n\u003cp\u003e The Pixel Tablet was Google\u0026#39;s first modern attempt at an Android tablet. And while it didn\u0026#39;t get everything right, it was still a pretty good piece of hardware. You get a vibrant 11-inch screen and powerful processor with Google\u0026#39;s Tensor G2 chip that\u0026#39;s paired with 8GB of RAM and 128GB of internal storage. \u003c/p\u003e    \u003cp\u003eThe software is also smooth, and you can run pretty much anything you need to on this tablet, whether you\u0026#39;re looking at productivity apps or even games. Of course, you also have cameras on this tablet as well, which can be used to capture the moment or have a video call with family, friends or even colleagues. \u003c/p\u003e    \u003cp\u003eOverall, this isn\u0026#39;t a bad tablet to go with if you\u0026#39;ve been looking for something affordable and by Google. It isn\u0026#39;t the latest tablet on the market, but there\u0026#39;s still plenty left in the tank, especially with Google\u0026#39;s reliable track record when it comes to software updates. Get it now for just $279 while this deal\u0026#39;s still live. \u003c/p\u003e    \u003c/div\u003e\n    \n                \n        \n        \n\n\n        \n\n\n\n\n\n                                            \n\n\n\n\n        \n    \u003c/article\u003e\n\n    \n            \n        \u003c/div\u003e\u003c/div\u003e",
